        "content": "<!--DOCTYPE html-->\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<title>Delhi's Best Street Shopping Hubs: From Sarojini Nagar to Lajpat Nagar</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"container\">\n    <h2>The Ultimate Guide to Bargain Street Shopping in Delhi</h2>\n    <p>Delhi is a paradise for shoppers, offering some of the most vibrant street markets in Asia. If you want to buy trendy clothes, traditional Indian wear, silver jewelry, or handicraft souvenirs without spending a fortune, street shopping is the way to go. Here is a curated guide to the best bargaining spots in the capital.</p>\n\n    <h3>1. Sarojini Nagar Market (SN)</h3>\n    <p>Famous for export surplus clothes, Sarojini is where you can buy global fashion brands at a fraction of their retail prices. T-shirts, dresses, and denim are sold here for as low as ₹100–300. The key to shopping here is scanning the piles and bargaining down to at least half of the vendor's initial quote.</p>\n\n    <h3>2. Janpath Market & Tibetan Market</h3>\n    <p>Located next to Connaught Place, Janpath is ideal for tourists. The main street has small boutique stalls selling embroidered bags, silver rings, brass ornaments, and ethnic shawls. The adjacent Tibetan market offers beautiful paintings, incense, and Himalayan beads.</p>\n\n    <h3>3. Lajpat Nagar (Central Market)</h3>\n    <p>If you are looking for authentic Indian ethnic wear (kurtis, sarees, salwar suits), Lajpat Nagar is unmatched. It is also famous for mehendi (henna) artists who sit along the pavements and create intricate designs on your hands in minutes.</p>\n\n    <div class=\"info-box\">\n        <strong>🛍️ Stay Close to the Bazaars</strong>\n        <p>A long day of street shopping and carrying bags can be exhausting. Plan ahead and <a href=\"https://gethotelstays.com/delhi\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: var(--accent); font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">book shopping-friendly hotels in South Delhi on GetHotelStays</a> so you can quickly drop off your purchases and refresh.</p>\n    </div>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>",
